40:08.262 --> 40:14.290
And I love that because as a believer, it is an image of us.

40:16.514 --> 40:27.449
See, like a lighthouse standing firm against all of the crashing waves, our hope remains unshaken because it's built on a foundation of God's love.

40:29.412 --> 40:42.650
If we are on solid ground, if we are on solid ground, we are a beacon that shines a light in a lost and dying world in the darkness.

40:43.952 --> 40:45.554
What's the darkness sin?

40:48.482 --> 40:55.651
And we stand as a beacon saying, hey, listen, there's dangerous waters out there.

40:56.552 --> 40:59.155
There are things out in the water that are trying to kill you.

40:59.495 --> 41:07.505
